==Spanish==

===Etymology===
Latin ''[[trahere]]''

===Verb===
'''traer'''

# to [[bring]]
# to [[attract]], to [[draw]], to [[pull]]
# to bring about, to [[cause]], to [[occasion]]
# to cause to be, to have in a certain condion
#:Oye, me traes intranquilo &mdash; ''You make me so restless.''
# to [[wear]] ''(clothes)''
# to bring forward, to [[advance]], to [[adduce]]
# to [[make]], to [[compel]], to [[oblige]]
# to [[persuade]]
# to [[have]], to [[carry]] ''(in a publication, in stock)''

